items.title: Asian shares are mixed after US stocks drift to more records
items.description: Asian shares are mixed in thin holiday trading, with most markets in the region and elsewhere closed for Christmas

items.title: Judge upholds Hawaii's new climate change tax on cruise passengers
items.description: A federal judge's ruling allows Hawaii's new tourist tax, which includes a levy on cruise ship passengers, to take effect in 2026

items.title: Telluride Ski Resort in Colorado to close Saturday due to labor dispute
items.description: Officials at Colorado's Telluride Ski Resort say it will close Saturday due to a labor dispute

items.title: US stocks drift to more records on a holiday-shortened day of trading
items.description: US stocks drifted higher to more records on a holiday-shortened day of trading

items.title: Average US long-term mortgage rate ticks down to 6.18% this week
items.description: The average rate on a 30-year U.S. mortgage ticked down modestly this week, remaining in the same narrow range of the past two months
